<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1600 GMT, April 30 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW -- The wounded Tajik President, Emomali Rakhmonov,
strongly condemned the terrorist attack in northern Tajikistan
early today which killed two people and injured 49, including the
president.
</P>
<P>
The terrorist action "was conducted by some individuals and
agent provocateurs who will be punished," said Rakhmonov, several
hours after the grenade attack, a plot to assassinate him, in the
town of Khudjand, Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Rakhmonov, 44, was wounded in the leg, and his life was not in
danger, his press secretary Zafar Saidov said.
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iranian President Akbar Hashemi Rafsanjani today
criticized the European countries for embarking on "childish
games."
</P>
<P>
"Iran had long ago stopped critical dialogue with the member
states of the European Union (EU)," said the Iranian president
while addressing the first conference on energy.
</P>
<P>
Suspension of the critical dialogue between EU and Iran is one
of the latest decisions made by the EU member states at the
ministerial meeting concluded in Luxembourg Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
BONN -- German Chancellor Helmut Kohl's party today angrily
denied French news reports that it had received millions of
dollars in illicit payments from the French oil company,
Elf-Aquitaine.
</P>
<P>
"This is an especially vicious rumor, ... an ugly fabrication
in which there is nothing," said Christian Democratic Union (CDU)
General Secretary Peter Hintze.
</P>
<P>
TIRANA -- A weapons depot exploded today in the central
Albanian town of Burrel, killing at least 20 people, police said.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the explosion was not immediately known. 
</P>
</TEXT>
