<HEADLINE> China Presents Sports Equipment to Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 30 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government today
presented 14 tonnes of sports equipment and a minibus worth
250,000 U.S. dollars to Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
At a handover ceremony in Harare, Chinese ambassador to
Zimbabwe Liu Guijin said, "this has demonstrated once again that
the bilateral relations between China and Zimbabwe in various
fields including sports are being further strengthened and
developed."
</P>
<P>
Now five Chinese coaches who specialized in swimming,
ping-pong, gymnastics, volley ball and martial arts respectively
have arrived in Zimbabwe. He hoped that they would become
goodwill ambassadors to promote the traditional friendship
between the two peoples and the understanding between the sports
circles of the two countries through their hard work.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his belief that the cooperation between the two
countries in the field of sports will surely achieve greater
success.
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwe's minister of sport, recreation and culture W.P.M.
Mangwende greatly appreciated the Chinese government's valuable
contribution which will give a tremendous boost to the
development of sports in Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
He also heartily welcomed the five Chinese coaches to
Zimbabwe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
