<HEADLINE> Two Killed in Explosion of Navy Sailing Barge off France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Two people were killed and three
reported missing in an explosion which took place this morning on
a sailing barge of the French Navy off the west coast port of
Cherbourg, reported Agence France-Presse (AFP).
</P>
<P>
The 630-ton barge, Fidele, was transporting explosives for
destruction in the sea, and was wrecked in the explosion which was
heard some 30 kilometers around, AFP quoted witnesses and
officials as saying.
</P>
<P>
The ship had on board 16 soldiers and six civilians when it
exploded, AFP quoted its captain as saying.
</P>
<P>
A British ship nearby helped rescue some of the survivors
together with some French fishing boats and rescue boats, but they
failed to find three people missing from the explosion.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the explosion is still undecided.  
</P>
</TEXT>
