<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Syrian FM Meets EU Mideast Envoy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Syrian Foreign Minister Farouq
al-Shara met here today with visiting EU Special Envoy to the
Middle East Miguel Angel Moratinos.
</P>
<P>
Shara and Moratinos discussed the latest developments in the
region and the serious crisis facing the peace process on account
of the Israeli government policies, according to the Syrian Arab
News Agency (SANA).
</P>
<P>
They also talked about Euro-Arab relations in the light of the
recently held Malta conference.
</P>
<P>
The EU envoy, who arrived here Tuesday from Jordan, declared
upon arrival that his visit to Syria was aimed at examining the
prospects of resuming negotiations along the Syrian-Israeli track.
</P>
<P>
The EU did not ignore the Syrian track, he said, adding that
there were good ideas and intentions to push the peace process
forward and to overcome the present impasse.
</P>
<P>
Moratinos is due to leave Damascus Saturday for Cairo for
talks with Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa on the latest
developments of the peace process. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
