<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Truck Carrying Explosives Overturns, No Injuries Reported </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 30 (Xinhua) -- A truck carrying 15,000 pounds
of ammonium nitrate and other explosives overturned near
Princeton, North Carolina, Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
All residents and businesses in the rural area within
three-quarters of a mile have been evacuated and aircraft were
banned from an area stretching a mile from the scene and 4,000
feet high minutes after the accident, The United Press
International reported.
</P>
<P>
North Carolina emergency management spokesman Tom Hegele said
there had been no reports of injuries from the scene.
</P>
<P>
The truck had left the main highway and reportedly was en route
to a rock quarry when it ran off a narrow two-lane road.
</P>
<P>
The explosives unit from Seymour Johnson Air Force in nearby
Goldsboro, North Carolina, has joined a state hazardous materials
team at the accident site to help dispose of the potentially
explosive materials.  
</P>
</TEXT>
