<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South African Deputy President to Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, April 30 (Xinhua) -- South African Deputy President
Thabo Mbeki and Minister of Transport and Communications Mac
Maharaj will pay a five-hour visit to Mozambique next Monday.
</P>
<P>
According to a press communique released by the Mozambican
Ministry of Transport and Communications, the South African
officials during their visit will meet with Mozambican Prime Minister
Pascoal Mocumbi, Minister of Transport and Communications Paulo
Muxanga and Minister of Public Works and Housing Roberto White.
</P>
<P>
The two sides will sign a passenger transport agreement and
a cargo transport agreement as well as a contract.
</P>
<P>
The contract is for the construction of the Maputo-Witbank
express highway which is one of the projects of the Maputo
Development Corridor (CDM). The CDM was first initiated on
February 19, 1996 and it requires an investment of over one
billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Mozambican President Joaquim Chissano and South African
President Nelson Mandela attended the meeting on the investment
</P>
<P>
The completion of CDM will not only benefit Mozambique in
many aspects but also provide a new convenient sea outlet for
South Afirca. 
</P>
</TEXT>
