<HEADLINE> First Egyptian Consignment of Vegetable Oil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, April 30 (Xinhua) -- The first consignment of
Egyptian vegetable oil, within the framework of the Iraqi-U.N.
oil-for-food agreement, arrived in Iraq today.
</P>
<P>
According to a statement by Awni Hashem, Director of the
Egyptian Trade Center here, the consignment, contracted by the
Iraqi Ministry of Commerce with the Egyptian Holding Company for
Foodstuff Industries, weighs 1,000 tonnes.
</P>
<P>
Hashem said that the rest of the contracted vegetable oil
consignments would arrive in Iraq through Jordan within the
coming few days.
</P>
<P>
Iraqi Minister of Commerce Mohammed Mehdi Saleh has announced
that large numbers of trucks are streaming into Iraq daily across
the crossing points on the borders with Jordan and Turkey,
carrying imported foodstuffs in implementation of the accord
signed by Iraq and the U.N. last May.
</P>
<P>
The oil-for-food deal allows Iraq to sell 2 billion
U.S. dollars worth of oil over six months to buy food and other
supplies for its people hit hard by the U.N. sanctions. 
</P>
