<HEADLINE> Turkish PM Condemns Terrorist Attack in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Turkey's pro-Islamic Prime
Minister Necmettin Erbakan today strongly condemned the terrorist
attack against Tajik President Emomali Rakhmonov.
</P>
<P>
In his letter to Rakhmonov, Erbakan said that this attack is
a great element threating international peace and stability,
adding that it is necessary for the international cooperation to
fight against terrorism.
</P>
<P>
The attack, in which two people were killed and 49 others,
including the president, injured, occurred at 10:30
a.m. local time (0530 GMT) when a lone assailant hurled a
grenade after Rakhmonov had got out of his car and was heading
for a theater for celebrations marking the 65th anniversary of
the Khudjand University.
</P>
<P>
The grenade landed near the president and other local leaders
when they were only a few steps from the entrance to the
theater, media reports said.
</P>
<P>
The attacker, identified as Firdavs Dustboboyev, 26, was
detained immediately after the incident. 
</P>
