<HEADLINE> Reestablishment of State Organs Inspiring </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, April 30 (Xinhua) -- The work to reestablish state
organs throughout Angola began today in Mbanza Congo, capital
of the Zaire province in northern Angola.
</P>
<P>
Government officials said this is encouraging.
</P>
<P>
Mbanza Congo used to be the capital of ancient Kingdom of
Congo, where kings of various dynasties lived. It is known
typically for African cultural relics.
</P>
<P>
Angolan vice-minister of territory administration Nzau Puna
said that to reestablish state organs in the areas occupied by
the National Union for Total Independence of Angola is an
important work set forth in the Lusaka Peace Agreement and the
beginning of this work is an important step for the solution of
other problems and also opens an extremely good perspective for
the smooth conclusion of the peace process.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Culture Maria De Oliveira said that today's
ceremony is an important action and will also create conditions
for the restoration of the historical relics in Mbanza Congo
known throughout the world.
</P>
<P>
The work to reestablish state organs was originally
scheduled to begin early in March. However, conditions were not
ripe. The formation of the Angolan government of national unity
and reconciliation on April 11 paved the way for the work.
</P>
</TEXT>
