<HEADLINE> Iran Terms EU Declaration Invalid, Unjustifiable </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Iran today condemned European
Union's (EU) decision to suspend dialog with Tehran, describing it
as "invalid and unjustifiable."
</P>
<P>
At the ministerial meeting concluded in Luxembourg Tuesday, the
European Union (EU) also decided to stop the ministerial level
contact between the two sides and continue its arms embargo on
Iran.
</P>
<P>
In response to EU's decision, the ministry said in a statement
that Iran will not tolerate any deviation from the norms of
inter-state conduct and principles of mutual respect and
non-interference.
</P>
<P>
"The Islamic Republic of Iran shall respond in the appropriate
reciprocal manner to any (EU's) measure," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The statement declared that "Iran will refrain from engaging in
any discussion over other subjects of critical dialog, including
human rights, terrorism, and conventional, nuclear and chemical
weapons with the European Union or its member states."
</P>
<P>
The statement described the EU decision as invalidly and
unjustifiably "constituting a grave breach of international law
and the norms governing the conduct of inter-state affairs."
</P>
<P>
The statement lashed out at the Berlin court verdict on the
Mykonos case and the EU's decision as "pure fabrications" and
"totally baseless."
</P>
<P>
The Berlin court verdict on April 10 implicated Iranian
leadership behind the assassination of four Kurdish opposition
leaders in Mykonos restaurant in 1992.
</P>
<P>
The statement claimed that the EU member countries provide
"full and public support" to terrorism to operate freely in their
territories against Iran, which is a major victim of terrorism.
</P>
</TEXT>
