<HEADLINE> Zambian Government Urged to Crop Killing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Villagers living along the
Zambezi river between Mwandi and Sesheke in Western province of
Zambia have appealed to the government to crop crocodiles which
have killed six people in the past two months.
</P>
<P>
People especially women and children are caught and killed
when they go to fetch water from the crocodile-infested river.
</P>
<P>
The villagers are worried that if no action is taken to crop
the reptiles, many more people will be killed.
</P>
<P>
Zambia Daily Mail today quoted a local official as saying "it
is better for crocodiles to be cropped than the crocodiles
cropping people. The government should immediately come to our
aid and crop these reptiles which have become a menace to human
life." 
