<HEADLINE> Malaria Kills 949 Zimbabweans This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 30 (Xinhua) -- At least 166 people died of
malaria throughout Zimbabwe during the past week, bringing the
total number of people who have died of the disease this year to
949.
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwe experienced some of its heaviest rains in many years
this season, creating hot and humid conditions suitable for
breeding of malaria-creating mosquitoes.
</P>
<P>
So bad is the situation that more than 40,255 malaria cases
were dealt with at hospitals throughout the country this week
alone, bringing the cumulative national malaria cases for 1997 to
380,323.
</P>
<P>
The deaths so far this year compare with the just over 2,000
recorded throughout the country last year.
</P>
<P>
However, the Ministry of Health and Child Welfare's weekly
disease update released today said in effect, the cumulative
malaria cases this week showed a downward trend, with a 14
percent decrease nationally. 
</P>
</TEXT>
