<HEADLINE> 4th OAU/ICRC Seminar on International </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Participants of the fourth
OAU-ICRC seminar on international humanitarian law here today
reiterated the need for the teaching of the international
humanitarian law and its wide dissemination.
</P>
<P>
This was contained in the recommendations made by the
participants at the end of the two-day seminar organized by the
Organization of African Unity (OAU) and the International
Committee of the Red Cross (ICRC).
</P>
<P>
The recommendations said the culture of peace should be carried
out through basic education, particularly at the level of youths.
</P>
<P>
The participants noted the international rules would be
ineffective if they were not accompanied by national
implementation measures.
</P>
<P>
The participants supported the international criminal tribunal
for Rwanda and took note of the difficulties faced by the members
of the tribunal in the fulfilment of their tasks.
</P>
<P>
They supported the idea of establishing a permanent
international tribunal which would supplement the work of the
national tribunals.
</P>
<P>
They also took note of the need for increasing material
and financial resources of the Arusha tribunal and for greater
cooperation among memebr states of the OAU.
</P>
<P>
The seminar requested these recommendations be appended to the
report of the OAU Commission of 20 on Refugees and be the subject of
a decision of the 66th Ordinary Session of the Council of Ministers
scheduled in Harare, Zimbabwe at the end of May 1997. enditem

