<HEADLINE> China, Syria to Jointly Set up Large Spinning Mill </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, April 30 (Xinhua) -- China and Syria today signed an
agreement to set up a 182-million-U.S. dollar spinning mill in the
Syrian coastal city of Jabalet.
</P>
<P>
An agreement was reached between the Chinese Company for
Textile Industries and Foreign Technical and Economic Cooperation
and Syria's Public Establishment for Textile Industries.
</P>
<P>
The signing ceremony was attended by Ahmad Nizameddin, Syrian
Minister of Industry, and the Chinese Ambassadress in Damascus Mrs
Wu Min Min.
</P>
<P>
At the end of the signing ceremony, the Syrian minister stated
that the projected spinning mill is one of the biggest of its kind
in Syria, and its annual output will be around 24,000 tonnes.
</P>
<P>
He added that Syria will seek to export the production of the
mill, pointing out that the Syrian government is endeavoring to
develop the Syrian weaving and spinning industries, and to
industrialize all of its ginned cotton. Last year's production of
Syrian cotton amounted to 640,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
The project is expected to be completed over a period of 30
months. 
