<P>
He pointed out that the policical relations that date back to
the early 60s were sufficent ground upon which to build strong
economic co-operation.
</P>
<P>
"It makes no economic sense for Tanzania to continue conducting
business with far away countries in Europe and elsewhere without
exploring the great potentials that exist in nearby Egypt," he said.
</P>
<P>
President Mkapa invited Egyptian investors to invest in
Tanzania's financial, mining, tourism sector and the agro-based
industry.
</P>
<P>
He gave an example of the abundant fruit varieties in Tanzania
which lacked the supportive canning industry, a situation that forces
Tanzanians to import juice from South Africa and Israel.
</P>
<P>
In reply, the Egypian foreign minister said his country has taken
note of the positive economic structural changes in Tanzania and had
decided to move in with great determination.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian minister said he was pleased that this visit
coincided with the meeting of the Tanzania-Egyptian joint
commission and the signing of trade protocals as the bases for
further economic ties.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he handed to President Mkapa a special message from
President Hosny Mubarak of Egypt.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was also attended by Tanzanian Minister for Foregin
Affairs and International Cooperation Jakaya Kikwete and Minister
of Finance Daniel Yona.  enditem

