<TEXT>
<P>
(by Wang Nengbiao)
</P>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Zambia called for promoting
trade relations between Zambia and China here today.
</P>
<P>
On the eve of the visit to Zambia by Chinese Premier Li Peng,
Zambian Commerce, Trade and Industry Minister Alfayo Hambayi said that
there is great potential for increasing and diversifying a two-way
trade between China and Zambia.
</P>
<P>
He told Chinese and local reporters that over the last three
decades Zambia has been exporting mainly copper and other metals to
China and importing from China mainly consumer goods, noting that "the
potential for trade in other products is there and should be exploited
by both countries."
</P>
<P>
