<HEADLINE> Torrential Rain Floods Most of Greek Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, April 30 (Xinhua) -- A rare heavy rainfall today
flooded the basement of flats and stores and put traffic lights
out of order on a number of streets in the Greek capital.
</P>
<P>
The worst hit occurred in the suburbs of Glyfada, Voula,
Ilioupolis and Argyrouplis, where the level of water on many
streets was over 40 centimetres.
</P>
<P>
In the seaside suburb of Voula, many cars could not move ahead
after roads were extensively flooded because drains quickly became
blocked.
</P>
<P>
In kifissos, a pile-up occurred which involves three trucks and
three cars, but no one was injured. 
