<HEADLINE> 93 People Die of Cholera in Tanzanian Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Ninety-three people have
died here of cholera and 1,927 others affected since January 29,
when the first case was reported.
</P>
<P>
The City Health Commissioner, Matiku Nyakarungu told the
official Daily News here today that 146 cholera victims were
still in health and emmergency centers in the city.
</P>
<P>
He said the situation has been aggravated by rains and failure by
the public to observe hygiene.
</P>
<P>
"Despite our massive mobilization and education on health rules to
curb the epidemic, most of the people have given deaf ear, and fallen
victims of the disease," he said.
</P>
<P>
Nyakarungu said the city commission had set emergency centers in
all heavily affected areas to minimize delays in treating the disease,
saying delays were among major causes of death.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the health commissioner thanked donor agencies for
monetary and material support which he said helped a great deal in
controlling the epidemic.  enditem

