<HEADLINE> Bildt Calls for Full Implementation of Bosnia Peace Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Carl Bildt, High
Representative for the Implementation of the Peace Agreement in
Bosnia and Herzegovina, today stressed the importance of full
implementation of the Bosnia peace accord.
</P>
<P>
"The peace process of Bosnia is moving forward, basically on
track," Bildt told reporters after briefing the 15 members of the
U.N. Security Council this morning.
</P>
<P>
"I have made clear that there is no alternative to the Dayton
road," the High Representative said. "Difficult as it will be, and
difficult as it is now."
</P>
<P>
The peace agreement to end the bloodshed conflict in the former
Yugoslav republic was reached after some two weeks of intense
negotiations among the three warring parties in Dayton, Ohio, in
November, 1995.
</P>
<P>
Bildt said that any sort or any resumption of use of force
would not be tolerated in Bosnia.
</P>
<P>
This is a clear message for the parties concerned, he added.
</P>
<P>
He also voiced strong objection to any attempt for the
domination of institutions by one group or another in Bosnia and
Herzegovina. 
</P>
</TEXT>
