<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Agreements on five projects
in the field of technical assistance were signed here today
between the governments of Germany and Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
According to a press release from the German Embassy here, the
agreements provide for new commitments of about 17.8 million
Denmarks and the prolongation of one project for which the German
government had already committed 5.7 million Denmarks.
</P>
<P>
The release said the total money on Germany's on-going
projects now reachs more than 170 million Denmarks.
</P>
<P>
The five projects focus on water supply,
food production and resource management. enditem

