<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Primakov, Albright Start Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Russian Foreign Minister Yevgeny
Primakov and visiting United States Secretary of State Madeleine
Albright started talks today, the Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The talks will focus on an agreement governing Russian-North
Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO) relations, European security
and Russian-U.S. relations.
</P>
<P>
During her last visit to Moscow, Albright and Primakov reached
an understanding in principle that a possible agreement between
Russia and NATO should be of legally-binding nature.
</P>
<P>
Before today's talks, Albright said she was not confident of
the agreement on Russian-NATO relations because the West had
already made every possible concession to Russia, said Itar-Tass.
</P>
<P>
The two foreign ministers are expected to hold a joint news
conference after the talks.
</P>
<P>
Albright arrived in Moscow earlier today. 
</P>
