<HEADLINE> Central Chinese Province to Have Six New Tourism Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Henan Province in Central China
has started the development of six major tourism projects that
make use of its historic and cultural heritage, according to
sources at the Provincial Tourism Administration.
</P>
<P>
They include: a panoramic view of the Yellow River in
Zhengzhou, the provincial capital, financed by the province and
Singapore; a site depicting the ancient culture in the Yellow
River-Heluo River area, in Luoyang, one of the seven well-known
ancient Chinese capitals; and a project in Kaifeng City based on
an ancient Chinese painting "River-Cruising in the Qingming
Festival" by Zhang Zeduan who lived in the Song Dynasty (960-1279).
</P>
<P>
The Xiaolangdi Hydro-electric power project now under
construction in Luoyang, will produce a large reservoir, a number
of islands, and many scenic spots. The authorities plan to turn
them into a 23-ha senic spot.
</P>
<P>
Two other projects include tourism facilities at Stone-Man
Mountain near Pingdingshan City, and a temple for Huangdi on Juci
Mountain, the legendary birthplace of this Chinese
ancestor. 
</P>
</TEXT>
