<HEADLINE> Australian Ministers Launch Attack On Hanson </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Senior officials of the Australian
Government today launched their most direct attack yet on
Independent MP Pauline Hanson, describing her as a threat to the
nation's future.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Minister Alexander Downer strongly criticized Hanson's
anti-immigration and anti-Aboriginal policies, saying "the simple
truth is that Hanson's policies are job-destroying policies".
</P>
<P>
Downer's remarks were made today while addressing a gathering
of Australian ambassadors from throughout Asia.
</P>
<P>
Victorian Premier Jeff Kennett accused Hanson of abusing
Australia's democratic traditions by seeking to divide society,
"she would have us pit ourselves against Aboriginal communities,
she has done so much damage in terms of relationships with those
Australians who are of Asian origin", Kennett said over radio.
</P>
<P>
The officials' attack on Hanson came after opinion polls showed
her support rising to between 10 and 25 percent of the electorate.
</P>
<P>
A Morgan Poll released in Tuesday suggested one in 10 people
would give their first preference to Hanson's One Nation Party,
while an AGB-McNair Poll found 25 percent of the respondents
supported Hanson. 
