<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 1 (Xinhua) -- The Pudong Branch of the Industrial
and Commercial Bank of China (ICBC) and the Shanghai Branch of
Japan's Tokyo-Mitsubishi Bank recently made their first joint
loans.
</P>
<P>
The 30 million yuan in loans went to the Shanghai Sharp
Electronics Co. Ltd., a Sino-Japanese joint venture and the
largest electrical home appliance exporter in China. They reflect
the changing pattern in Chinese and foreign bank cooperation in
the Pudong New Area, one Japanese banker observed.
</P>
<P>
Ten million yuan of the loans is coming from the Japanese side.
</P>
<P>
