<HEADLINE> Japanese Labor Groups Mark May Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, May 1 (Xinhua) -- An estimated 631,000 people today
attended more than 570 rallies held by labor unions all over
Japan, marking May Day.
</P>
<P>
In Tokyo, three of the largest groups in Japan led the 68th May
day events held in various parks.
</P>
<P>
