<HEADLINE> Wages Data Send Australian Dollar Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, May 1 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar closed firmer
as a sharp rise in wage growth reported today headed off chances
of a cut in interest rates next week.
</P>
<P>
The local unit closed at 78.45 U.S. cents from 78.20 at the
close Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
With unemployment at 8.7 percent and the inflation outlook
previously unblemished, many in the market were tipping a 50-50
chance of a rate cut, but March quarter wages data released today
wiped out the chance of a rate cut.
</P>
<P>
The growth of 1.3 percent surprised the financial markets where
the highest forecast had been a quarterly rise of 1.0 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar also hit a five-year high against the
Japanese yen, ending at 99.95 from 99.21, and against the German
mark it closed at 1.3591 from 1.3493.  
