<HEADLINE> HK Monetary Authority Launches Revamped Website </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 1 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Monetary Authority
(HKMA) launched today a revamped HKMA website carrying more
interactive and comprehensive information on the HKMA.
</P>
<P>
The website contains updated information on the structure,
activities and publications of the HKMA and it permits online
access to the 1996 HKMA Annual Report released Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman said that the website offered a new section on the
annual meetings of the World Bank and International Monetary Fund
which will be held in Hong Kong on September 23-25 this year.
</P>
<P>
The section has information on the meeting schedule and the
social and cultural events as well as facilities available at the
Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center and its new extension
built at a cost of 620 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that the page is also linked to the
International Monetary Fund's Dissemination Standard Bulletin
Board which provides the economic and financial statistics and the
methodology employed by economies including Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
He said that other features include a new section on Hong
Kong's monetary arrangements through 1997, video clips of senior
executives and extracts from HKMA publications.
</P>
<P>
Joseph Yam, chief executive of the HKMA, said that the HKMA
decided to revamp the site in order to provide more information
and keep the world posted on the latest development of the
monetary and banking systems in Hong Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
