<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanzania, Egypt Sign Cooperation Agreements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Egypt and Tanzania signed six
co-operation agreemnts in several fields in Arusha, Northern
Tanzania on Wednesday to consolidate bilateral ties between the
two countries, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The agreements involve tourism, economic and technical
co-operation, promotiona and protection of investment,
information and cultural and scientific co-operation.
</P>
<P>
The agreements were signed at Mount Meru Hotel in Arusha by
the Egyptian Foreign Minister Amir Moussa on behalf of his
government and the Tanzania Foreign Minister Jakaya Kikwete on
bedhalf of Tanzania government.
</P>
<P>
On tourism co-opeation, the agreement covered, among other
things, collaboration in promotion and marketing, education and
training, exchange of information and co-operation in the
international fora.
</P>
<P>
The agreement covered availability of water for agriculture in
the field of economic and technical co-operation.
</P>
<P>
Covered in the same field also were resources for health
development, electricity and energy as well as trade.
</P>
<P>
In the information field, the two countries agreed to exchange
radio and TV programs, training and study visits. Also covered in the
agreements were areas of culture, scientific co-operation and
education.
</P>
<P>
The two countries also agreed to co-operate in the promotion
and protection of investment both in the private sector and the
business community as a locomotive engine for the establishment
of solid commercial and investment relation between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
According to a statement issued at the end of the session, an
agreement on co-operation between chambers of commerce of the two
countries, would be signed at a date and venue to be determined
later by the two sides.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian foreign minister and his delegation arrived in
Tanzania on Tuesday for a two-day official visit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
