<HEADLINE> Crimes at Johannesburg International Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Crimes at Johannesburg Airport
have increased remarkably since 1994, with at least 10,295
criminal cases registered during the period, local daily the
Citizen reported today.
</P>
<P>
The average daily number of crimes at Johannesburg Airport,
which is the gateway to the Southern African region for foreign
visitors, has risen from 8.5 cases in 1994 to 11 cases currently,
among which 958 arrests have been made, according to Jessie
Duarte, a security official in Gauteng Province.
</P>
<P>
Crimes at the airport include vehicle, baggage and cargo
theft.
</P>
<P>
An estimated 250 foreign victims have been recorded at the
airport since 1994, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
