<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Longyan City at Prefecture Level Established </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, May 1 (Xinhua) -- The prefecture-level Longyan City,
located in the western part of east China's Fujian Province, was
established today, with the approval from the State Council.
</P>
<P>
A grand ceremony was held today to mark the establishment of
the new city.
</P>
<P>
Longyan, well-known hometown of the Hakkas people and hometown
of many Chinese nationals residing abroad, is one of Fujian's
major forest area with many mineral resources and tourist
attractions.
</P>
<P>
Longyan is the hub of communications linking up with Fujian,
Guangdong and Jiangxi provinces.
</P>
<P>
The new city has a land space of 19,000 square kilometers and a
population of 2.83 million.
</P>
<P>
The original Longyan Prefecture has stopped its function and
the original county-level Longyan City has become a district of
the new city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
