<HEADLINE> Voters Begin to Cast Ballots in Britain's Election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Britain's 44 million voters began to
cast their ballots in around 45,000 polling stations nationwide
today in the long-awaited general election.
</P>
<P>
They will choose between the ruling Conservatives and the major
opposition Labor Party to form a government for the next five
years.
</P>
<P>
Around 3,700 candidates have registered to run for 659 seats in
the House of Commons and those who get most votes in each
single-seat constituency wins.
</P>
<P>
The election results will come out on Friday.
</P>
<P>
In 1992, 77.8 percent of the electorate of 43.2 million voted
and the Conservatives won 336 seats in the lower house and Labor
272. 
</P>
