<HEADLINE> Guilin-Liuzhou Expressway Opens to Traffic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, May 1 (Xinhua) -- The Guilin-Liuzhou expressway, the
first expressway in south China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous
Region, opened to traffic today.
</P>
<P>
The 138.5-kilometer-long road has four lanes and is 24.5 meters
in width.
</P>
<P>
It links up Guilin, the well-known tourism city famous for its
beautiful mountains and Lijiang River and Liuzhou City, a
commercial center in the region.
</P>
<P>
The construction of the expressway, running through five
mountains and crossing six rivers, started in October, 1993 and
the project absorbed 1.86 billion yuan (232 million dollars) of
investment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
