<HEADLINE> Urgent: Zaire's Peace Talks Postponed to Saturday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, May 1 (Xinhua) -- The Zairean government today
announced to postpone peace talks between Zairean President
Mobutu Sese Seko and rebel leader Laurent Kabila till Saturday,
according to a report reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
"The president is not leaving and the journey is canceled for
today. We understand the talks have been postponed until
Saturday," Information Minister Kin-Kiey Mulumba said in Zairean
capital Kinshasa.
</P>
<P>
Mobutu postponed his scheduled departure to Libreville, Gabon,
today and officials said his scheduled talks with Kabila had been
put back a day from Friday to Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
