<HEADLINE> Ugandan Rebel Commanders Charged With Treason </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Eighteen top commanders of the West
Nile Bank Front (WNBF) rebel movement have been charged with
treason in Uganda, local newspaper the New Vision reported today.
</P>
<P>
Chief Magistrate Flavia Munaaba told the accused that the
charge is of capital nature judged by high court to which they
can take plea after commitment for trial.
</P>
<P>
Betty Khisa, the state attorney, accused them for launching a
war against the state from 1995 to 1997 in Arua District,
northwestern Uganda.
</P>
<P>
WNBF, a crippled rebel group, has lost its main forces in
series of operations against the government troops in
northwestern Uganda. Most of its members are now under detention
in uganda. 
</P>
