<HEADLINE> Hong Kong to Hold Money World Asia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 1 (Xinhua) -- The 2nd Money World Asia, an
international trade fair focusing on money, investment and
financial services, will be held here later this month.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman of the Hong Kong Trade Development Council (TDC)
said that the fair is the region's premier money and investment
event that demonstrates Hong Kong's strength as a leading
financial center in Asia.
</P>
<P>
Alan Wong, assistant executive director of TDC's services
promotion, said that Money World Asia will be a platform for
buyers and sellers in the financial markets to have direct and
open access to each other.
</P>
<P>
During the three-day event, about one hundred local and
international organizations and companies will offer a
comprehensive range of financial services and money-related
products, including consumer and corporate banking, equity
investment, fund management, commodities, forex trading and money
collectibles.
</P>
<P>
Among the exhibitors of the fair are banks and financial
institutions, government and regulatory bodies, asset management
companies, insurance companies, stock exchanges and listed
companies.
</P>
<P>
According to Wong, several banks from the Chinese mainland will
participate in the People's Bank of China Pavilion, including
People's Bank of China, Bank of China, the Industrial and
Commercial Bank of China, Agricultural Bank of China and China
Construction Bank.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the exhibition, a series of seminars on different
aspects of financial and investment services will be organized for
both professionals and individual investors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
