<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Peng Zhen's Remains To Be Cremated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 1 (Xinhua) -- The remains of Peng Zhen, China's
outstanding leader who passed away on April 26 at the age of 95,
will be cremated on May 5 in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Peng Zhen was a great proletarian revolutionary and statesman,
an outstanding activist in state affairs, a staunch Marxist, a
major founder of the socialist legal system in China, and an
outstanding leader of the Communist Party of China and the state.
</P>
<P>
To mourn for Peng Zhen, national flags will be flown at
half-mast on May 5 at the Tian'anmen Square in Beijing, the
Xinhuamen Gate, the Great Hall of the People, the Ministry of
Foreign Affairs, at Party and government offices of various
provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities throughout the
country, at ports of entry, air and sea ports, and at China's
embassies and consulates in other countries, the Hong Kong Bureau
of the Xinhua News Agency, and the Macao Bureau of the Xinhua News
Agency. 
</P>
</TEXT>
