<HEADLINE> San Francisco Bids for 2008 Olympic Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 30 (Xinhua) -- San Francisco has joined other
U.S. cities to bid for the 2008 Olympic Games, local reports said
on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Bay Area Sports Organising Committee said it has raised the
requested 100,000 US dollars due on May 1, which enables San
Francisco into the initial bidding process.
</P>
<P>
As a procedure, every U.S. bidder must pay 100,000 US dollars
to the National Olympic Committee by the May 1 deadline, with the
latter recommending one of them to the International Olympics
Committee later.
</P>
<P>
So far, many American cities have expressed interest in hosting
the 2008 Games, including Cincinnati, Boston, Houston, New York
and Seattle. 
</P>
