<HEADLINE> Brazil Nips Mexico in Soccer Friendly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 30 (Xinhua) -- World champions Brazil had a
convincing victory of 4-0 over Mexico in a soccer friendly in
Miami on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Striker Romario scored a hat trick as the 1994 World Cup
winning squad surged ahead 3-0 in the first 20 minutes.
</P>
<P>
As an automatic qualifier for the 1998 World Cup finals, Brazil
had scored four goals in each of their previous friendlies at home
to Poland and Chile.
</P>
<P>
Midfielder Djalminha set up the first goal in the fifth minute
with a through pass to Leonardo, who scored with a right-foot shot.
</P>
<P>
Seven minutes later, Romario was fooled in the penalty box and
he himself kicked in the spot.
</P>
<P>
He added the third five minutes later from the edge of the area
and completed his hat-trick fifteen minutes from time from a pass
off Ronaldo.
</P>
<P>
It was Romario's fifth goal in three games since he made his
international comeback this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
