<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Condemns Attack on Tajik President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Iran today condemned an
assassination attempt on Tajik President Emomali Rakhmonov, who
suffered a minor leg injury from a hand grenade Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Iran's official news agency IRNA reported Mahmoud Mohammadi,
spokesman for the Iranian Foreign Ministry, denounced such violent
acts, expressing hope that the belligerent Tajik sides will do all
in their power to safeguard the achievements of the peace talks
until national reconciliation is full in place in Tajikistan.
</P>
<P>
The Tajik president was wounded in the legs Wednesday by a
hand grenade thrown at his feet as he got out of a car during a
visit to the northern town of Khojand.
</P>
<P>
Two people were killed and 60 others injured in the attack.
</P>
<P>
The assassination attempt against Rakhmonov came at a time
when his hard-line government has been negotiating a peace
settlement with opposition groups that have been waging civil
war since 1992 in the impoverished Central Asian nation.
</P>
<P>
As a mediator, Iran had provided offices and other
facilities for the peace talks between the Tajik government and
the opposition groups in the past few months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
