<HEADLINE> Bulls Enters Semis in Eastern Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Michael Jordan scored 28
points to pace Chicago Bulls for a 96-95 hard win over Washington
Bullets on Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
With the bare-knuckled win, the Bulls completed their sweep of
the first round series and await the winner of the Atlanta-Detroit
series in the Eastern Conference.
</P>
<P>
Scottie Pippen scored 20 points, including the basket that
clinched the best-of-five series.
</P>
<P>
Rod Strickland had 24 points and nine assists for Washington,
which was hosting its first playoff game in nine years.
</P>
<P>
The Bullets blew a nine-point lead with four minutes left and
were swept by a combined 18 points by the defending NBA champions.
</P>
<P>
It was the end of an era for the Bullets, who next season are
changing their nickname to Wizards.
</P>
<P>
In Portland, Kenny Anderson scored 30 points as Portland Trail
Blazers went on to defeat Los Angeles Lakers 98-90, which kept
their in the Western Conference first-round series wherein Los
Angeles led the best-of-five series 2-1. 
