<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Major Route for Drug Smuggling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
(by Cai Guozhong)
</P>
<P>
KAMPALA, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Uganda has in recent years become a
major international route for smuggling of narcotics including
heroin, cocaine, Mandrax and cannabis from Latin America and Asia
to Europe and the United States.
</P>
<P>
As it is difficult for drug traffickers to smuggle narcotics
directly from Latin America or Asia to Europe and U.S.A., Uganda
became an important transit point for the traffickers.
</P>
<P>
Due to backwardness and lack of drug detection equipment, east
African countries, especially Uganda, have been a very
appropriate conduit for smugglers to ferry drugs outside.
</P>
<P>
The trend of drug smuggling through Uganda is very worrying.
In 1996, 12 foreign and 298 Ugandan smugglers were arrested and
prosecuted in Uganda.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the Ugandan authorities intercepted 3.7 kilograms
of heroin worth 82,000 U.S. Dollars, over 78 kilograms of Mandrax
tablets worth 679,000 Dollars, about four kilograms of cocaine
worth 800,000 Dollars, among others.
</P>
<P>
Because Uganda is backward in technology of detecting narcotic
drugs, only one out of ten smugglers have been arrested in the
country while nine have escaped legal punishment.
</P>
<P>
Traffickers usually export drugs disguised as tea, vanilla or
sesame to northern America or Europe through Uganda.
</P>
<P>
The amount of drugs seized by Ugandan Anti-Narcotic Unit are
on rise. For instance, the amount of heroine seized by the unit
increased from 2.8 kgs in 1994 to 3.2 kgs.
</P>
<P>
Another reason for the increase of drug smuggling is that the
powerful Colombian "Cali Cartel", an international drug smuggling
group, is behind the movement of cocaine and heroine through
Uganda.
</P>
<P>
In order to fight drug smuggling, the unit bought high-powered
speed motor boats in 1994 to help curb increasing drug smuggling
on Lake Victoria.
</P>
<P>
A lot of smuggled goods including narcotic drugs are coming
through Lake Victoria from Kenya to Uganda's landing site
Bukakata on shore of the lake, then move by road to other places
including Kampala and the Entebbe International Airport.
</P>
<P>
The Ugandan government has also sent some members of the unit
to Europe to learn how to fight drug trafficking.
</P>
<P>
After Zambia and South Africa, Uganda has already established
a national coordinating commission to combat drug abuse.
</P>
<P>
Uganda's fighting against drug smuggling has got supports from
the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations Drug Control Program (UNDCP) has since
early 1990s given material support to Uganda in its effort to
combat drug smuggling, and the United Nations Development Program
(UNDP) in July 1996 donated five motorcycles and one Hyunda
vehicle to the drug control project in the country's police
anti-narcotic unit.
</P>
<P>
However, anti-drug smuggling is a global issue. Nearly 150
billion U.S. Dollars worth of illicit drugs are sold worldwide
today, according to the UNDP.
</P>
<P>
Uganda, as a major conduit for narcotic drug trafficking in
the world, is facing an extremely hard and bitter struggle
against narcotic drug trafficking. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970501.0158 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-01 </DATE_TIME>
