<HEADLINE> Nanning Invests in a New Look </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 1 (Xinhua)-- Nanning, capital of China's Guangxi
Zhuang Autonomous Region, will invest 1.85 billion yuan in 10
urban engineering projects this year, according to the current
issue of "The Great Southwest Economic Reporter."
</P>
<P>
The projects range from environment, telecommunications, water
conservation to tourist sites.
</P>
<P>
A key project is to build a 37-km-long city ring road, which is
to be completed within the year.
</P>
<P>
Another major project is the Qingchuan Bridge, which will open
to traffic on July 1.
</P>
<P>
The municipal government will also speed up construction of the
Qingxiushan holiday villages, dredge sludge out of the riverbed of
Nanhu Lake, build a sewage disposal project, and plant trees
around Nanhu Lake. 
</P>
