<HEADLINE> Peru Defeats Colombia in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Peru scored one goal to defeat
Colombia on Wednesday night, the first-ever win in 15 years.
</P>
<P>
With the victory, Peru improved its slate to 3-3-4 with 13
points, remained in contention for a spot in the 1998 World Cup
finals in France.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, Colombia that suffered its third straight
defeat in the World Cup qualifying, kept its second place with
5-3-2 on 17 points.
</P>
<P>
Paraguay that beat Uruguay 3-1, was the group runners with 23
points, as top four members will qualify for the finals.
</P>
<P>
Played at Barranquilla, Colombia, Jose Pereda scored the lone
goal at 62nd minute.
</P>
<P>
Colombia dominated the first half with crisp passes and solid
defense, but felt the loss of star striker Faustino Asprilla, who
was handed a two-game suspension for brawling earlier this month
with Paraguay's goalkeeper. 
</P>
