<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Zambia has restored trade links with
Burundi on specific commodities that are not affected by the
general embargo imposed on its military government nine months
ago, Zambian Foreign Minister L. Shimba announced on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
He said products allowed to be shipped to Burundi include food
products, items relating to education and construction materials
as well as medicine and agricultural products.
</P>
<P>
Shimba said the new measure taken by the Zambian government was
intended to reduce the suffering of the ordinary people in
Burundi.
</P>
<P>
Sanctions on Burundi have been imposed since a summit meeting
of countries in the Great Lakes region in central Africa nine
months ago to urge the Burundi military government to restore
civilian rule and national reconciliation. 
