<HEADLINE> May Day Celebrations in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan people are celebrating
the International Labor Day today with processions and rallies
amidst tight security precautions.
</P>
<P>
May Day celebrations are traditionally a show of strength by
various political parties in Sri Lanka. There are usually marches
and processions through the streets, and public meetings are held
under the banners of the different political parties.
</P>
<P>
Over 20 rallies and five processions will be held today by
major political parties and trade unions marking the event with
meetings at different venues in Colombo, the capital city of Sri
Lanka.
</P>
<P>
The ruling People's Alliance (PA) is scheduled to hold its
rally at the Colombo Town Hall grounds. This year's May Day theme
of the PA is "peace through development."
</P>
<P>
President Chandrika Kumaratunga is expected to preside over the
PA's rally. The rally will be preceded by a procession through the
streets of Colombo this afternoon, according to informed sources.
</P>
<P>
The main opposition United National Party will be holding its
May Day rally in the Central province plantation town of Hatton,
90 kilometers from Colombo, presided over by Opposition leader
Ranil Wickremesinghe.
</P>
<P>
The Ceylon Worker's Congress which derives its strength from
the plantations will also hold its rally in the nearby town of
Talawakelle.
</P>
<P>
Colombo went under a maximum security alert last night as
preparations for today's celebrations went on. Over 10,000
policemen and army soldiers were deployed to beef up security in
the whole city.
</P>
<P>
Rallies are being planned in provinces mainly by the Tamil
political parties. The Eelam Peoples Democratic Party and People
Liberation Organization of Tamil Eelam will hold their rallies in
the north and the east of the country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
