<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tajik Opposition Condemns Terrorist Act </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 30 (Xinhua) -- The Tajik opposition today
condemned the attempt on the life of President Emomali Rakhmonov,
in Khudjand, a northern city of Tajikistan, saying it is "a purely
criminal act."
</P>
<P>
The attack occurred at 10:30 a.m. local time (0530 GMT) when a
lone assailant hurled a grenade at President Rakhmonov, who was
getting out of his car at a theater to attend celebrations marking
the 65th anniversary of the Khudjand University.
</P>
<P>
Two people were killed and more than 60 were wounded.
</P>
<P>
The attacker, identified as Firdavs Dustboboyev, 26, was
detained immediately after the incident.
</P>
<P>
In a telephone interview with the Itar-Tass, opposition
alliance leader Abdumalik Abdulladjanov ruled out a political
motivation of the assassination and said the opposition has
nothing to do with criminals.
</P>
<P>
Abdulladjanov said the opposition alliance and his party
National Revival "have always been and will continue to be against
resolving problems by forcible means."
</P>
<P>
Tajik presidential spokesman Zafar Saidov called the
assassination attempt "an open political action."
</P>
<P>
Rakhmonov, who was wounded in the leg, vowed that the
terrorists will be severely punished.
</P>
<P>
Describing the situation in Tajikistan as "extremely complex,"
Abdulladjanov said the terrorist action might have been caused by
a complicated social and economic situation in the nation.
</P>
<P>
The opposition leaders said the attack was possibly related to
the recent events in Khudjand city where security forces killed
around 20 prisoners, who rioted in a local prison.
</P>
<P>
Earlier today, Russian President Boris Yeltsin also condemned
the terrorist action against Rakhmonov. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
