<HEADLINE> Romania, Moldova to Cooperate in Combating Crime </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Romania and Moldova signed a
protocol today on cooperation in combating transnational crimes in
1997-1998.
</P>
<P>
The two countries agreed to exchange information on crimes
committed on their respective territories and abroad and agreed on
measures to be taken against organized crimes.
</P>
<P>
The protocol was signed by Romanian Interior Minister Gavril
Dejeu and his Moldovan counterpart Mihai Plamadeala.
</P>
<P>
Dejeu told reporters after signing the document that Romania
and its neighbors, Moldova and Ukraine, are likely to take
concerted actions in fighting organized transnational crimes.
</P>
<P>
He said Romania and Moldova would also cooperate in interior
ministry personnel training. 
</P>
