<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe's Agricultural Sector to Grow by 12.8 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's agricultural sector is
this year expected to grow by about 12.8 percent with sugar as
its biggest contributor, local newspaper the Business Herald
reported today.
</P>
<P>
Sugar output is expected to rise by 87 percent to 630,000
tons. The increased output will see sugar contributing 8.5
percent to the growth of the agricultural sector this year.
</P>
<P>
Further significant contributions are expected from tobacco
and horticulture which are projected to grow by eight and 18
percent respectively in volume terms.
</P>
<P>
Despite the slight reduction in maize yields, supply is
expected to be greater than domestic demand mainly because maize
stocks from last year are still relatively high. 
</P>
</TEXT>
