<HEADLINE> Thai Workers Celebrate Labor Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Tens of thousands of Thai workers
today gathered at Sanam Luang, a large plot of open public land in
front of the Grand Palace, and adjacent avenues to celebrate the
International Labor Day.
</P>
<P>
The festivities, organized by the government and labor
organizations, began with religious rites and followed by parades,
festive activities and sports events.
</P>
<P>
Popular singers and dancers took to the stage to entertain
labor day revelers.
</P>
<P>
Labor leaders presented the government with a list of 20
demands for improving the status of workers, in particular in the
private sector.
</P>
<P>
The demands covered a wide rang of matters, including annual
adjustment of minimum wages, work safety, limiting migrant workers
to jobs in agricultural, construction and fishing fields, low-cost
of housing units for workers, introducing benefits fund to cover
retirement and the welfare of workers' children and unemployment,
and signing international conventions to certify workers' rights
for groupings and negotiations.  
</P>
