<HEADLINE> Asian Rubber Producers to Discuss Prices </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, May 1 (Xinhua) -- Asian natural rubber producers will
hold a periodic meeting soon to discuss the prices of the
commodity which have recently declined sharply on the world
market, an official said.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, which will be attended by rubber businessmen from
Indonesia, Malaysia, Singapore and Thailand, is expected to be
held in Hadjay, Thailand on May 2, General Secretary of the
Indonesian Rubber Dealers Association (Gapkindo) Local Chapter
Syarbaini Zeing said Wednesday in Medan, North Sumatra, according
to reports reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
The main topic of the meeting will concern the decline of the
prices of natural rubber on the world market as a result of
increased rubber supply from other producers in the American
region.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, Gapkindo will propose a restriction on natural
rubber supply to raise the prices of the commodity on the world
market.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia's natural rubber output in 1996 reached 1.5 million
tons.
</P>
<P>
The world's biggest natural rubber producer was still Thailand
which in 1996 produced 1.7 million tons.  
</P>
