Nicaragua) but will soon be turned over to the Department of
Migration," Gasteazoro said.
</P>
<P>
He said these problems will terminate when border limits in the
disputed Gulf of Fonseca and the Pacific coastal waters, which is
also shared with El Salvador, will be finally marked with buoys.
