<HEADLINE> International Automotive Technology Exhibition Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 1 (Xinhua) -- China International Automotive
Technology Exhibition and Vehicle Emission Control Symposium
opened in the Beijing Exhibition Center today.
</P>
<P>
More than 150 automobile companies and emission control
facility makers from over 20 countries and regions are attending
the four-day exhibition and the symposium.
</P>
<P>
They include Volkswagen from Germany, US Ford Motor Company,
several Sino-foreign automobile joint ventures and a number of
world famous emission control facility makers.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, the first of its kind in China, is jointly
sponsored by eight ministries and commissions including the State
Science and Technology Commission (SSTC), Ministry of Machinery
Industry and State Bureau of Environmental Protection (SBEP).
</P>
<P>
During the symposium, more than 300 experts and scholars on
automotive environmental protection will launch technological and
academic exchanges on motor vehicles and environmental protection,
regulations and standards of emission control, in a bid to seek
solution to China's control of air pollution caused by the tail
gas.
</P>
<P>
International organizations concerned and some foreign
governments and related associations including the World Bank,
European Union, World Motor Emission Control Association, and the
US, Sweden and France have sent senior officials or experts to
attend the exhibition.
</P>
<P>
China has an annual automotive manufacturing output of 1.4
million and keeps 10 million motor vehicles so far. The tail gas
has become one of the major pollutants in the city as a result of
the rapidly increasing number of cars in the urban areas.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has been paying great attention to the
vehicle emission control. Aided by the World Bank, the SSTC and
SBEP have arranged research on emission control. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
