<HEADLINE> Slovenia to Join Multinational Mission in Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Slovenia will become the ninth
nation to join the Multinational Protection Force (MPF) in Albania
under a decision made here today by the mission's directive
committee.
</P>
<P>
In a communique, the committee welcomed Slovenia's
participation in the MPF and stressed the importance of creating
an Albanian police force to ensure law and order in the Balkan
state.
</P>
<P>
Albania has been gripped by chaos and violence since the
failure of shady savings schemes last month, and thousands of
refugees have since fled the country to Italy and Greece.
</P>
<P>
The committee said the MPF's mission has been a political and
military success.
</P>
<P>
The quick deployment of the MPF, formed by Italy, Romania,
Greece, Turkey, Spain, France, Austria and Denmark, has improved
the distribution of humanitarian aid, reduced the number of armed
incidents and ensured a "general stabilization" of the situation
in Albania, the committee said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
