active stance on industrial policy as the public backlash
continues over BHP's decision to shut its Newcastle steelmaking
plants.
</P>
<P>
The Age
</P>
<P>
-- The Melbourne Airport is set to be sold to the AMP Society,
Australia's biggest investor, and the British airport company BBC
in a deal worth more than 1.3 billion Australian dollars (1.01
billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Australian Financial Review
</P>
<P>
-- Prime Minister John Howard has opened the door for Kerry
Packer to take control of the John Fairfax publishing group,
claiming that no one was running the company and that lifting all
ownership restrictions could leave the entire Australian media in
foreign hands.  
</P>
