<HEADLINE> Record-Breaking Sugar Cane Harvest in Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, April 30 (Xinhua) -- The production of sugar cane
in Brazil will reach a record-breaking 14.2 million tons, 5 percent
more than the yield during the previous harvest.
</P>
<P>
60 percent of the sugar cane is earmarked for the production
of alcohol and 40 percent to sugar, said Julio Maria Borges,
director of a Brazilian consulting firm which specializes in sugar
and alcohol.
</P>
<P>
The production of alcohol totaled 14 billion liters during the
previous harvest cycle and is expected to increase 7 percent this
year. Brazil is the largest producer of sugar cane in the world.
</P>
</TEXT>
