<HEADLINE> Germany Downs Ukraine in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Germany defeated Ukraine 2-0 in
Bremen on Wednesday, moving to second place in the World Cup group
nine qualifying tournament.
</P>
<P>
After a scoreless first half, Oliver Bierhoff netted the opener
with his left-foot shot off a perfect header from Juergen
Klinsmann in the 62nd minute.
</P>
<P>
Klinsmann made the second goal for Mario Basler 10 minutes
later who looped over Ukraine goalkeeper Olexander Kosovsky to put
Germany 2-0 up.
</P>
<P>
Germany moved to second place in the group with 11 points as
they collected the third victory in five outings.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine held the top spot with 12 points from six matches.
</P>
<P>
The two squads will meet each other again on June 7 in Kiev.
</P>
