<HEADLINE> Argentina Issues 400 Million Dollars Worth of Eurobonds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, April 30 (Xinhua) -- The government of Argentina
issued today a yen-denominated Eurobond for an amount equivalent
to 400 million U.S. dollars, the Economy Ministry said.
</P>
<P>
The Eurobond can be exchanged after seven years and will pay 9.49
percent per year of interest, 276 basis points above the U.S.
Treasury Bill, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
The European branch of the International Yamaichi Bank is
responsible for the arrangement of the bond issue which will be
regulated under British legislation. 
</P>
