<HEADLINE> Bosnia, Cuba Establish Diplomatic Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SARAJEVO, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Representatives of Bosnia and
Cuba have signed a protocol on the establishment of diplomatic
relations between the two countries, it was reported today.
</P>
<P>
The document was signed Tuesday in the Cuban embassy in
Vienna, according to the Sarajevo news agency ONASA.
</P>
<P>
Cuba recognized Bosnia's independence in December 1992 and is
the 115th country to establish diplomatic ties with the former
Yugoslav republic, ONASA said. 
