<HEADLINE> Senate Confirms Labor Secretary Nomination </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 30 (Xinhua) -- Alexis Herman today won
Senate confirmation to be secretary of labor following months of
waiting.
</P>
<P>
Senate Republicans lifted their holds on the nomination only
after the White House agreed to pull back an executive order that
would have favored organized labor in winning federal contracts
and will issue instead a presidential memorandum.
</P>
<P>
Republican critics described the order as a "payback" to labor
groups for backing U.S. President Bill Clinton in November. The
memorandum is seen as a concession because it is a temporary
measure.
</P>
<P>
Republicans made it clear that they were not opposing Herman so
much as using her nomination, stalled for nearly three months, as
a bargaining chip to force President Clinton to back down on his
executive order. 
</P>
</TEXT>
