<HEADLINE> Angolan Govt Sets Up State Organs in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, April 30 (Xinhua) -- The Angolan government set up
a provincial administrative organ in Zaire Province today,
heralding the beginning of reconstruction of its national power
structure in ex-rebel-controlled areas.
</P>
<P>
Members of the provincial government attended a rally
in Mbanza Congo, the provincial capital, occupied by the
former rebel National Union for the Total Independence of Angola
(UNITA), the Angolan News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Angolan Minister of Administration of Territory Faustino
Muteka said at the rally that the move indicates the
progress toward a lasting peace and will increase Angolans'
faith to peace.
</P>
<P>
Now, the provincial government can start work and give
priorities to food, sanitary, education and other problems on
people's livelihood, he said.
</P>
<P>
UNITA representative General Gabriel Samy said that the
re-establishment of a government in Zaire Province is of great
importance to the peace process in the country which has suffered
from nearly 20 years of civil war.
</P>
<P>
It is a victory for all Angolans, not for a certain party, he
said, warning the new government faces tough challenges to
enhance socio-economic development in the province. enditem

